The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                The driver of a Dum Dum-bound Metro Railway train slammed emergency brakes and saved a man who had jumped on the tracks at Kalighat station to commit suicide on Sunday afternoon. While the train was entering the station at 3.40pm, driver R.P. Dutta and assistant driver K. Biswas spotted the 46-year-old Belgachhia resident jump on the tracks at the other end of the platform. Dutta slammed the brakes and the train stopped around 20ft from him.     An elderly couple who had been staying on a playground in Barasat for the past few days after allegedly being thrown out of their rented house were brought to the local police station on Sunday. Bijoy Bose, 82, and wife Kalpana, in her 70s, told the police that their landlord had evicted them as they had failed to pay the rent. An NGO has told police it wants to take the couples responsibility.    Fan spares worth Rs 1 lakh were stolen from a shop in Thakurpukur on Saturday night. The owner told police that the robbers had tied up the four guards and looted the shop.                                                                                                                                               
